fx-Telarana Repository License Policy

This repository is mixed-license by path and artifact type.

Apache-2.0 applies to:
- smart contracts under contracts/src/ and contracts/script/
- Uniswap v4 hooks and hook-adjacent protocol code
- public Solidity protocol libraries and interfaces
- the public @bu/fx-engine SDK source, ABI modules, address registry, and helpers

AGPL-3.0-only applies to:
- backend services
- Hono APIs and API route implementations
- indexers, monitors, and offchain event processors
- agent, automation, simulator, deployment, Tenderly, Circle registration, and workflow services

MIT applies to:
- examples
- templates
- frontend demo components
- throwaway integration samples that are not production protocol code

When a file has an SPDX header, that header is authoritative for that file.
When a package has its own package.json license field, that package manifest is
authoritative for its published artifact. Vendored third-party code keeps its
upstream license, SPDX headers, copyright notices, and NOTICE requirements.

Full license texts:
- Apache-2.0: LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt
- AGPL-3.0-only: LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-only.txt
- MIT: LICENSES/MIT.txt
